  "description": [
    "Monday September 23 1918 WOMEN WILL FILL PLAGES OF AAEN IN iusefoboh May Publish Names of Men Do ing Nonessential Work That no man shall occupy the posi tion which can be filled by a woman is the intent of an order sent out to state and community labor boards by the U S employment service Wash ington Monday Fred French secretary local labor board said Monday while definite in structions had not yet been received preparation had been made for listing all men in nonessential employment as a result of the enlarged army program under which 4000000 men will be sent to France by next June The use of the term nonessential employ ment in the new instructions to com munity boards according to Washing ton advice has a special significance Although a man is working in a muni tion factory and even in making shells he still may be classified as a non essential worker This will occur when the community boards survey shows a mans job can be filled by a woman WOMEN MUST HELP The program really means women of the nation are to muster to help turn out shells In making surveys the boards ac"
